Deliverables:
- Frontend components & pages (React components + styles) with tests.
- Backend routes, DB migrations, token lifecycle logic, email templates, and tests.
- Documentation: configuration options (token TTL, rate limits), environment variables (EMAIL_PROVIDER, RESET_TOKEN_PEPPER, RESET_TOKEN_TTL), and operational runbook for investigating reset abuse.
- Post-deployment checklist: verify email deliverability, inspect logs for reset requests, monitor metrics for spikes, and ensure links operate correctly in production domain.

Notes for implementer:
- Prefer Argon2 for password hashing if available; otherwise bcrypt with current safe work factor.
- Use a server-side "pepper" in addition to hashing to make DB leaks less useful.
- Keep token raw value ephemeral (only returned in email). Do not log raw token.
- Coordinate with infra team to ensure rate limiting is enforceable at the edge (API gateway) for better resilience. for style.

